  <name>Pomodoro Timer</name>
  <summary>A GNOME Pomodoro timer with 20-20-20 rule reminders</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      A native GNOME application that implements the Pomodoro Technique with integrated 
      20-20-20 rule reminders for eye health. Every 20 minutes, the app reminds you to 
      look at something 20 feet away for 20 seconds to reduce eye strain.
    </p>
    <p>Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Customizable Pomodoro timer (default 25 minutes)</li>
      <li>20-20-20 rule notifications every 20 minutes</li>
      <li>Native GNOME integration with libadwaita</li>
      <li>Audio and visual notifications</li>
      <li>Persistent notifications that require acknowledgment</li>
    </ul>
  </description>
